rows.questionText: What is the primary purpose of AI Safety?
rows.options: ["To make AI systems faster", "To ensure AI systems operate reliably, ethically, and without causing unintended harm", "To reduce the cost of AI development", "To replace human workers with AI"]
rows.explanation: AI Safety focuses on ensuring AI systems are reliable, ethical, and don't cause unintended harm to humans or society.

rows.questionText: Which of the following is NOT a reason why AI Safety matters?
rows.options: ["Preventing harm at scale", "Building public trust in AI", "Maximizing AI company profits", "Regulatory compliance"]
rows.explanation: While AI safety may indirectly benefit companies, its primary purposes are preventing harm, building trust, and ensuring compliance.

rows.questionText: What is the maximum penalty under the EU AI Act for prohibited AI practices?
rows.options: ["€10 million or 2% of global revenue", "€35 million or 7% of global revenue", "€50 million or 10% of global revenue", "€1 million or 0.5% of global revenue"]
rows.explanation: The EU AI Act imposes penalties up to €35 million or 7% of global annual revenue for prohibited AI practices.
